"The user browses View 1 at the Overview level and learns about the overall distribution of crop productivity across districts and seasons. Next, the user selects a district or season of interest in View 1, and this interaction filters data in View 2, View 3, and View 4. In View 2, the user observes seasonal yield trends for selected crops at the Exploration level. In View 3 and View 4, the user investigates the correlation between cultivation area and yield and analyzes yield per hectare across districts and seasons. Finally, the user uses View 5 at the Detail level to inspect yield distribution for specific crops with highlighted outliers."